{{Infobox award | name = Bonei Zion Prize | image = Bonei-zion-logo.png | description = Awarded annually to formally recognize the achievements of outstanding Anglo immigrants and their contribution to the State of [[Israel]]. | presenter = [[Nefesh B'Nefesh|Nefesh B'Nefesh nonprofit organization]] | country = [[Israel]] | year = 2013 | website = {{URL|http://www.nbn.org.il/bonei-zion/}} }}
The [[Sylvan Adams]] '''Bonei Zion Prize''' ({{lang-he-n|'''פרס בוני ציון'''}}; Translation: ''Builders of Zion Prize'') is awarded annually by the [[Nefesh B'Nefesh]] organization to formally recognize the achievements of outstanding Anglo immigrants and their contribution to the State of [[Israel]]. A Prize is awarded in each of the following categories: "Culture, Art & Sports", Young Leadership, Science an Medicine, Israel Advocacy, Business & Technology, Education, Community & Non-profit, Lifetime Achievement.<ref name="official">{{cite web|url=http://www.nbn.org.il/bonei-zion/|title=Bonei Zion Prize|publisher=[[Nefesh B'Nefesh]]|access-date=5 May 2018}}</ref><ref name="jpost">{{cite web|url=https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Winners-of-Nefesh-BNefesh-Bonei-Zion-award-announced-450261|title=WINNERS OF SYLVAN ADAMS NEFESH B’NEFESH BONEI ZION AWARD ANNOUNCED|first=SAM|last=SOKOL|publisher=[[The Jerusalem Post]]|date=5 April 2016|access-date=5 May 2018}}</ref><ref name="arutz7">{{cite web|url=https://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/News.aspx/245324|title=2018 Bonei Zion Prize recipients announced|publisher=[[Arutz Sheva]]|date=2 May 2018|access-date=5 May 2018}}</ref>
