[[Image:Johann Adam von Ickstatt.jpg|thumb|Johann Adam von Ickstatt]]
'''Johann Adam Freiherr von Ickstatt''' (6 January 1702 &ndash; 17 August 1776) was a [[Germany|German]] [[educator]] and director of the [[University of Ingolstadt]]. Born in [[Eppstein|Vockenhausen]], he was a major proponent of the [[Age of Enlightenment|Enlightenment]] in [[Bavaria]].  He died in [[Waldsassen]].  He was a [[Godparent|godfather]] to [[Adam Weishaupt]].

