'''Linda M. Hunt''' is a professor of anthropology specializing in [[Medical anthropology]] at [[Michigan State University]].<ref>[http://anthropology.msu.edu/blog/people/huntli/  - Linda Hunt - Professor.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310001211/http://anthropology.msu.edu/blog/people/huntli/ |date=2014-03-10 }}</ref> She teaches and researches on [[Medical Anthropology]], Minority Health Research and Research Methods in Cultural Anthropology.<ref>[https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23804331 Genes, race, and culture in clinical care: r... &#91;Med Anthropol Q. 2013&#93; - PubMed - NCBI]</ref><ref>[http://scholars.opb.msu.edu/expert.asp?n=Linda+M+Hunt&u_id=61&oe_id=1&o_id=2 Linda M Hunt - Michigan State University - SciVal Experts 4.6] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426234115/http://scholars.opb.msu.edu/expert.asp?n=Linda+M+Hunt&u_id=61&oe_id=1&o_id=2 |date=2014-04-26 }}</ref> She has been researching issues related to diabetes management, the use race and genetics in clinical care, and pharmaceuticalization, among others.<ref>[https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs11013-012-9303-x Pharmacogenetics in Primary Care: The Promise of Personalized Medicine and the Reality of Racial Profiling - Springer]</ref>

