ra|National Convention Centre]] | align=center|1980 | align=center|M/F |- | '''[[Brazil Open (squash)|Brazil Open]] | {{BRA}} | [[Rio de Janero|Rio]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|1993 | align=center|M |- | '''[[JSM Super Squash]] | {{JPN}} | [[Yokohama]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|1994 | align=center|M |- | '''[[Mahindra International]] | {{IND}} | [[Bombay]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|1994 | align=center|M |- | '''[[Al-Ahram International]] | {{EGY}} | [[Cairo]] | [[Giza Plateau]] <small>(in front of the [[Egyptian pyramids|pyramids]])</small> | align=center|1996 | align=center|M/F |- | '''[[Pakistan International]] | {{PAK}} | [[Islamabad]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|1999 | align=center|M |- | '''[[PSA Masters]] | {{flagicon|EGY}} / {{flagicon|QAT}} / {{flagicon|BER}} / {{flagicon|IND}} | [[New Delhi]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|2000 | align=center|M |- | '''[[Kuwait PSA Cup]] | {{KUW}} | [[Kuwait City]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|2004 | align=center|M |- | '''[[Saudi International]] | {{KSA}} | [[Al Khobar]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|2005 | align=center|M |- | '''[[Sky Open]] | {{EGY}} | [[Cairo]] | align=center|<small>''/''</small> | align=center|2008 | align=center|M |- | '''[[British Grand Prix (squash)|British Grand Prix]] | {{ENG}} | [[Manchester]] | [[National Squash Centre]] | align=center|2010 | align=center|M |}
==PSA World Series Ranking Points== PSA World Series events also have a separate World Series ranking. Points for this are calculated on a cumulative basis after each World Series event. The top eight players at the end of the calendar year are then eligible to play in the [[World Series Squash Finals|PSA World Series Finals]].
